# Built artifacts — the dos-hook binary is built locally (GHF1) and, until GHF4
# ships it in the plugin bundle, is not committed. Never commit a compiled binary.
#
# NOTE the leading slash: `/dos-hook` anchors to the `go/` ROOT, so it ignores the
# built `go/dos-hook` binary WITHOUT matching the `go/cmd/dos-hook/` SOURCE directory
# (an unanchored `dos-hook` would ignore that dir and silently drop main.go — the bug
# this anchoring fixes).
/dos-hook
/dos-hook.exe
/dos-hook-*
# Go test artifacts.
*.test
*.test.exe
/hooktest.exe
*.out
